Can generalize “Gini” approximation obtain formula? First, note x y axis go 0 1, area +B therefore always 0.5 (\(1\times 1\times 0.5=0.5\)), can therefore write:\[\begin{align}
    Gini&=/(+B)\nonumber\\
    &=/0.5\nonumber\\
    &=1-2B
\end{align}\]simply used since \(+B=0.5\) \(=0.5-B\). Now just need find area \(B\). First, let us define household \('s\) income (wealth) \(y_i\), sorted households according income (wealth) rank. first household (one lowest income wealth) following contribution area B:\[\begin{align}
  b_1=\frac{y_1}{\sum_i^ny_i}
\end{align}\]second household contribute following value:\[\begin{align}
  b_2=\frac{y_1+y_2}{\sum_i^ny_i}
\end{align}\]finally, sum households get:\[\begin{align}
  B=&\frac{1}{n}\frac{y_1}{\sum_i^ny_i}+\frac{1}{n}\frac{y_1+y_2}{\sum_i^ny_i}+\dots+\frac{1}{n}\frac{y_1+y_2+\dots+y_n}{\sum_i^ny_i}\nonumber\\
  B=&\frac{1}{n}\frac{y_1+y_1+y_2+\dots y_1+y_2+\dots+y_n}{\sum_i^ny_i}\nonumber\\
  B=&\frac{1}{n}\frac{ny_1+(n-1)y_2+\dots+y_n}{\sum_i^ny_i}\nonumber\\
  B=&\frac{1}{n}\frac{\sum_i^n(n-+1)y_i}{\sum_i^ny_i}\nonumber\\
\end{align}\]can insert expression \(Gini\) get expression approximate Gini coefficient:\[\begin{align}
    Gini&=1-\frac{2}{n}\frac{\sum_i^n(n-+1)y_i}{\sum_i^ny_i}\nonumber
\end{align}\]important note formula approximation based bar chart approach. work well long number bars sufficiently large. many formulas Gini coefficient. simple straightforward, formulas give precise estimates. formula tends overestimate area B, approximating area using height right end bars (small improvement simply use average height bar height lagged bar).good Gini coefficient? First , Gini coefficient just one number, thus easy compare across countries time. Secondly, satisfies number key principles: () independent country’s size currency used, (B) rich household transfers money poor household Gini reduced (C) anonymous (say anything poorest richest households ).Gini coefficient perfect measure inequality? ! Institutional settings differ considerably. health care country financed affect inequality. health care privately funded, take large share low income households, relatively low share high income households. hand, health care financed progressive income tax case.Another issue Gini coefficient depends quality data. calculated based deciles () considerably less precise calculated based thousands observations.

